parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rupture of brake lines can cause sudden and complete loss of brake action, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake action
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning light illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
vehicle skids or loses control when applying brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of brake fluid can cause a sudden loss of brake pressure, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
loss of brake pressure
brake fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.

loss of brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause loss of vehicle control, especially in panic braking situations, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the ABS system fails to engage
the vehicle experiences reduced braking performance
the brakes feel spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front drive shaft can cause loss of power to the wheels, leading to reduced vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences vibrations or shaking
the vehicle has difficulty moving or loses power
the drive shaft breaks or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idler arm can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Excessive play in the steering
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the idler arm breaks or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod end can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The tie rod end breaks or fails
the vehicle experiences loss of steering control
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical connectors can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to reduced vehicle performance and safety.
symptoms: The electrical connectors overheat or melt
the blower switch fails
the vehicle experiences electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat track can cause the seat to break or recline unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control while driving or increasing the risk of injury in the event of a rear-end collision.
symptoms: The seatback falls or reclines unexpectedly
the seat track breaks or cracks
the seat adjuster fails
the support bolt shears off
the seat moves unexpectedly while driving.
